abroad /əˈbrɔːd/

1. ADV If you go abroad , you go to a foreign country, usually one that is separated from the country where you live by an ocean or a sea. 到国外 

例： I would love to go abroad this year, perhaps to the South of France. 我今年想去国外，可能去法国南部。 

例： He will stand in for Mr. Goh when he is abroad. 当高先生在国外时他将代行其职。

